<li><a href="/wiki/Richard_Hofstadter" title="Richard Hofstadter">Richard Hofstadter</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/Anti-intellectualism_in_American_Life" title="Anti-intellectualism in American Life">Anti-intellectualism in American Life</a>.</i> New York: Alfred A. Knopf, 1963.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Susan_Jacoby" title="Susan Jacoby">Susan Jacoby</a>, <i>The Age of American Unreason.</i> New York: Pantheon Books, 2008.</li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAaron_Lecklider2013" class="citation book cs1">Aaron Lecklider (2013). <i>Inventing the Egghead: The Battle over Brainpower in American Culture</i>. Philadelphia: University of Pennsylvania Press. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-8122-4486-1" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-8122-4486-1"><bdi>978-0-8122-4486-1</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Inventing+the+Egghead%3A+The+Battle+over+Brainpower+in+American+Culture&amp;rft.pub=Philadelphia%3A+University+of+Pennsylvania+Press&amp;rft.date=2013&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-8122-4486-1&amp;rft.au=Aaron+Lecklider&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAnti-intellectualism" class="Z3988"></span></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFElvin_T._Lim2008" class="citation book cs1">Elvin T. Lim (2008). <span class="id-lock-registration" title="Free registration required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/antiintellectual0000lime"><i>The Anti-Intellectual Presidency: The Decline of Presidential Rhetoric from George Washington to George W. Bush</i></a></span>. New York: Oxford University Press. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0199898091" title="Special:BookSources/978-0199898091"><bdi>978-0199898091</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Anti-Intellectual+Presidency%3A+The+Decline+of+Presidential+Rhetoric+from+George+Washington+to+George+W.+Bush&amp;rft.pub=New+York%3A+Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.isbn=978-0199898091&amp;rft.au=Elvin+T.+Lim&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fantiintellectual0000lime&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAnti-intellectualism" class="Z3988"></span></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/wired-success/201407/anti-intellectualism-and-the-dumbing-down-america">"Anti-Intellectualism and the "Dumbing Down" of America"</a>. psychology today. 2014. <q>There is a growing and disturbing trend of anti-intellectual elitism in American culture. It's the dismissal of science, the arts, and humanities and their replacement by entertainment, self-righteousness, ignorance, and deliberate gullibility.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Anti-Intellectualism+and+the+%22Dumbing+Down%22+of+America&amp;rft.pub=psychology+today&amp;rft.date=2014&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.psychologytoday.com%2Fblog%2Fwired-success%2F201407%2Fanti-intellectualism-and-the-dumbing-down-america&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAnti-intellectualism" class="Z3988"></span></li></ul>
